# Error Handling

## Error Class Hierarchy

```
GmoAozoraError (base)
├── GmoAozoraAuthError           — OAuth/token failures
│   ├── GmoAozoraStateMismatchError  — PKCE state parameter mismatch
├── GmoAozoraApiError            — API returned an error response
│   ├── GmoAozoraValidationError     — 400 Bad Request
│   ├── GmoAozoraPermissionError     — 403 Forbidden
│   ├── GmoAozoraNotFoundError       — 404 Not Found
│   ├── GmoAozoraConflictError       — 409 Conflict
│   └── GmoAozoraRateLimitError      — 429 Too Many Requests
├── GmoAozoraServerError         — 5xx, retriable
├── GmoAozoraTimeoutError        — pollResult exceeded timeoutMs
├── GmoAozoraValidationError     — Zod schema validation failure on response
└── GmoAozoraWebhookError
    ├── GmoAozoraWebhookSignatureError  — HMAC mismatch
    └── GmoAozoraWebhookParseError      — Valid sig, invalid JSON
```

## Base Error Shape

Every error must include:

```typescript
class GmoAozoraError extends Error {
  readonly code: string;
  readonly requestId?: string;
  readonly cause?: unknown;
}
```

`requestId` comes from the `x-request-id` header on the API response.
Include it whenever available — it's the key to correlating logs.

## Throwing

Always use a specific error class:

```typescript
// ✅ Typed, structured
throw new GmoAozoraAuthError({
  code: 'REFRESH_FAILED',
  message: 'Token refresh failed: invalid_grant',
  requestId,
});

// ❌ Opaque
throw new Error('refresh failed');
```

## Catching

Re-narrow the error type in catch blocks:

```typescript
try {
  await client.corporation.balances.get();
} catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof GmoAozoraRateLimitError) {
    await sleep(e.retryAfterMs ?? 1000);
    // retry
  } else if (e instanceof GmoAozoraError) {
    logger.error('api_error', { code: e.code, requestId: e.requestId });
    throw e;
  }
  throw e; // re-throw unknown errors — never swallow them
}
```

Never `catch { /* nothing */ }`. Every error is either handled or re-thrown.

## Serialization

Errors must be JSON-serializable for logging:

```typescript
// ✅ Structured log entry
logger.error('transfer_failed', {
  code: e.code,
  message: e.message,
  requestId: e.requestId,
});

// ❌ Raw error object — may not serialize cleanly
logger.error('transfer_failed', { error: e });
```
